    <!-- AyudaActivity -->
    <string name="ayuda_titulo">HELP AND USER MANUAL</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_nav_titulo">1. General Navigation</string>
    <string name="ayuda_nav_desc">Swipe from the left edge of the screen to the right, or tap the menu icon (☰) in the top left corner, to open the Main Menu. From there you can access all sections of the application.</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_lista_titulo">2. Bird Guide</string>
    <string name="ayuda_lista_desc">In the \"Bird Guide\" you will find a complete catalog of birds. Select any bird to see a detailed technical sheet that includes its scientific name, family, and high definition photographs obtained directly from Wikipedia.</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_ia_titulo">3. Smart Chat (Gemini AI)</string>
    <string name="ayuda_ia_desc">Do you have questions about ornithology or a particular species? Access the \"Chat with AI\" screen to chat with our artificial intelligence, powered by Google Gemini, ready to answer your questions instantly.</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_anadir_titulo">4. Add Birds</string>
    <string name="ayuda_anadir_desc">From the main screen you can log your own sightings in the Pinto database. Write the bird\'s name, assign its species, detail its measurements and provide a description. You can save the changes and the bird will be automatically added to the Guide.</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_favoritos_titulo">5. Favorite Birds</string>
    <string name="ayuda_favoritos_desc">Inside any bird\'s profile, you will see a star icon. If you tap it, you will save that species to your personal list. You can quickly access all your saved species from the \"Favorites\" screen in the main menu.</string>
    
    <string name="ayuda_buscador_titulo">6. Search and Advanced Filters</string>
    <string name="ayuda_buscador_desc">In both the General Guide and your Favorites, you have a search bar to instantly filter the list by the bird\'s name. Additionally, tapping the funnel icon lets you cross-reference taxonomic filters (Family and Order) and even find birds that do not exceed specific measurements (Length and Wingspan).</string>

    <string name="ayuda_ajustes_titulo">7. App Settings</string>
    <string name="ayuda_ajustes_desc">In the \"Settings\" section you can customize how the application works, such as changing the language between Spanish and English with immediate application on all screens. You can also manage your session here.</string>

