    <string name="quiz_q1_q">What is the scientific name of the Great Bustard?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q1_opts"><item>Otis tarda</item><item>Tetrax tetrax</item><item>Ciconia ciconia</item><item>Alectoris rufa</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q2_q">The Great Bustard is considered one of the heaviest flying birds in the world. In what type of habitat is it mainly found?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q2_opts"><item>Dense forests</item><item>Cereal steppes</item><item>Coastal areas</item><item>High mountains</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q3_q">To which order does the Great Bustard belong?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q3_opts"><item>Passeriformes</item><item>Otidiformes</item><item>Ciconiiformes</item><item>Falconiformes</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q4_q">What is the scientific name of the Red-legged Partridge?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q4_opts"><item>Perdix perdix</item><item>Alectoris rufa</item><item>Coturnix coturnix</item><item>Phasianus colchicus</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q5_q">What does the Red-legged Partridge mainly feed on?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q5_opts"><item>Small fish</item><item>Insects and small mammals</item><item>Seeds, shoots and small invertebrates</item><item>Exclusively fruits</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q6_q">What is the scientific name of the White Stork?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q6_opts"><item>Ciconia nigra</item><item>Ciconia ciconia</item><item>Mycteria ibis</item><item>Ardea cinerea</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q7_q">The White Stork is considered the most popular animal of Pinto\'s wildlife. Where does it usually build its nest?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q7_opts"><item>In underground burrows</item><item>On roofs, towers and high poles</item><item>In bushes at ground level</item><item>On coastal cliffs</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q8_q">To which family does the White Stork belong?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q8_opts"><item>Ardeidae</item><item>Threskiornithidae</item><item>Ciconiidae</item><item>Accipitridae</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q9_q">What is the scientific name of the Little Bustard?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q9_opts"><item>Otis tarda</item><item>Tetrax tetrax</item><item>Burhinus oedicnemus</item><item>Pterocles orientalis</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q10_q">The Little Bustard is a typical bird of the Pinto steppes. What characteristic does its flight have?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q10_opts"><item>Glides for hours without flapping its wings</item><item>Produces a characteristic whistle with its wings when flying</item><item>Only flies at night</item><item>Flies exclusively in V formation</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q11_q">What is the scientific name of the Great Spotted Cuckoo?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q11_opts"><item>Cuculus canorus</item><item>Clamator glandarius</item><item>Upupa epops</item><item>Merops apiaster</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q12_q">The Great Spotted Cuckoo has a very peculiar reproductive behavior. What is it?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q12_opts"><item>Builds highly elaborate hanging nests</item><item>It is a brood parasite: it lays its eggs in the nests of other birds</item><item>Incubates the eggs in the hot sand</item><item>Both parents take turns incubating for 24 hours</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q13_q">What is the scientific name of the European Goldfinch?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q13_opts"><item>Serinus serinus</item><item>Carduelis carduelis</item><item>Fringilla coelebs</item><item>Chloris chloris</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q14_q">Which plant does the European Goldfinch show a special preference for feeding on?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q14_opts"><item>Oak</item><item>Thistle</item><item>Holm oak</item><item>Olive tree</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q15_q">What characteristic color does the European Goldfinch\'s face have?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q15_opts"><item>Deep blue</item><item>Red, white and black</item><item>Uniform yellow</item><item>Emerald green</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q16_q">What is the scientific name of the Red Kite?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q16_opts"><item>Milvus migrans</item><item>Milvus milvus</item><item>Aquila chrysaetos</item><item>Circus aeruginosus</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q17_q">What shape is the Red Kite\'s tail, which helps identify it in flight?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q17_opts"><item>Rounded</item><item>Square</item><item>Forked</item><item>Pointed</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q18_q">What is the scientific name of the Hen Harrier?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q18_opts"><item>Circus pygargus</item><item>Circus aeruginosus</item><item>Circus cyaneus</item><item>Accipiter gentilis</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q19_q">What physical feature easily distinguishes the Northern Lapwing?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q19_opts"><item>A long curved bill</item><item>A crest or tuft on the head</item><item>Red webbed feet</item><item>Completely white plumage</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q20_q">What is the scientific name of the Common Buzzard?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q20_opts"><item>Buteo buteo</item><item>Falco peregrinus</item><item>Aquila pennata</item><item>Milvus migrans</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q21_q">What does the Common Buzzard mainly feed on?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q21_opts"><item>Fish and amphibians</item><item>Fruits and seeds</item><item>Small rodents</item><item>Aquatic insects</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q22_q">What flight capability is typical of the Common Kestrel to locate its prey?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q22_opts"><item>Flies in an upward spiral</item><item>Hovers in the air (stationary flight)</item><item>Flies low over water</item><item>Performs dives at over 300 km/h</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q23_q">What is the scientific name of the Little Owl?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q23_opts"><item>Strix aluco</item><item>Tyto alba</item><item>Athene noctua</item><item>Bubo bubo</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q24_q">At what time of day is the Little Owl most active?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q24_opts"><item>Exclusively at night</item><item>At dawn and dusk (crepuscular)</item><item>Only at noon</item><item>Only during storms</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q25_q">What physical trait gives the Crested Lark its Spanish name (Cogujada)?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q25_opts"><item>Its very long tail</item><item>Its pointed crest (cogujada)</item><item>Its curved beak</item><item>Its red legs</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q26_q">What is the scientific name of the House Sparrow?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q26_opts"><item>Passer montanus</item><item>Passer domesticus</item><item>Petronia petronia</item><item>Sturnus vulgaris</item></string-array>
    
    <string name="quiz_q27_q">What characteristic white mark does the Common Wood Pigeon have on its neck?</string>
    <string-array name="quiz_q27_opts"><item>A vertical line</item><item>White patches on both sides of the neck</item><item>A complete white collar</item><item>It has no white marks</item></string-array>
